# Project Structure Guide

This is an Eleventy-based static site project with the following key directories:

- `src/`: Main source directory containing all site content and templates
  - `assets/`: Static assets like images, fonts, and other media
  - `data/`: Global data files used across the site
  - `includes/`: Reusable template components
  - `layouts/`: Base layout templates
  - `pages/`: Main page content
  - `writing/`: Blog posts and articles
  - `work/`: Portfolio work items
  - `functions/`: Custom JavaScript functions

- `dist/`: Build output directory (generated)
- `static/`: Static files that are copied directly to the output
- `utils/`: Utility functions and helpers

Key configuration files:
- [.eleventy.js](mdc:.eleventy.js): Main Eleventy configuration
- [package.json](mdc:package.json): Project dependencies and scripts
- [netlify.toml](mdc:netlify.toml): Netlify deployment configuration
